Subject: [eVuln] CALimba Authentication Bypass Vulnerability


New eVuln Advisory:
CALimba Authentication Bypass Vulnerability
http://evuln.com/vulns/68/summary.html

--------------------Summary----------------
eVuln ID: EV0068
CVE: CVE-2006-0693
Software: CALimba
Sowtware's Web Site: http://www.errebit.com/opensource/index.php?rb=calimba
Versions: 0.99.2, 0.99.1 and earlier
Critical Level: Moderate
Type: SQL Injection
Class: Remote
Status: Unpatched. Developer(s) contacted.
Exploit: Available
Solution: Not Available
Discovered by: Aliaksandr Hartsuyeu (eVuln.com)

-----------------Description---------------
Vulnerable script: rb/cls/rb_auth.php

Variables $login $password are not properly sanitized before being used in a SQL query. This can be used to pass authorization or make any SQL query by injecting arbitrary SQL code.

Condition: magic_quotes_gpc - off

--------------Exploit----------------------
Available at: http://evuln.com/vulns/68/exploit.html

--------------Solution---------------------
No Patch available.

--------------Credit-----------------------
Discovered by: Aliaksandr Hartsuyeu (eVuln.com)


